f=Engineering/dana/custom/migration-discipline/assets/migration-script-template.md · h1:Migration Script [name] [store] [date]=Rail artifact. dana authors; OPERATOR runs. Reversible (tested down-script) explicit operator sign-off recovery plan. Sequenced expand→migrate→contract. · h2:Effect summary (plain language operator approves THIS)=[What does, human terms. Tables/collections/edges affected. Estimated rows. What explicitly touch. Reversible? yes/no.] · h2:Up-script=`[the forward migration — in the store's language: SQL / HelixQL / migration DSL]` · h2:Down-script (reversible)=`[the rollback — restores the prior schema/state]` · h2:Down-script (reversible)=Down tested scratch/restored copy: evidence ref untested DONE, irreversible: operator sign-off ref [___] recovery plan [___] risk entry [___] · h2:Sequencing=Phase: [expand migrate contract], step independently rollback-able: explanation · h2:Execution (Rail 3)=Authored by: dana, **TO RUN BY: OPERATOR** (dana execute environment, urgency exception), Operator approved: ___ Operator ran: date ___ · h2:Post-run verification=\| expected (from summary) \| actual \| match \| · h2:Post-run verification=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Post-run verification=\| \| \| ✓/✗ → incident if ✗ \| · h2:Post-run verification=ops deploy record: [ref] quinn gate evidence: [ref]